    "body": "The bug still exists for me, however the problem of the chain being out of sync with many inbound connections has been resolved. The chain used to stall when my outbound connections would dwindle to around 1 or 0 despite having many inbound connections, but now the chain stays synced with 0 outbound, with around 100 inbound connections. This is after running 1.1.0 for about 36 hours, where it used to stall with 1.0.1 around an hour, no matter the number of inbound connections (outbound would always trickle to 0 and inbound connections would not sync). \n\nIn other words, it looks like this is now a non issue if port forwarding is configured properly because the inbound peers are always diligent to sync the chain. The lack of outbound connections still raises an eyebrow though.\n\nEdit: the version I'm actually running is 1.1.0, and I've been running it for a few days which trickled down to only inbound peers, but the chain is still kept up to date.\n",
