    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In that log, the original issue where discovery stopped working is no longer present.\n\nBut here's another observation:\nThe log covers 145 seconds of execution. Within that time, there were 8 distinct cases where a block you received had a future timestamp. The error message is a bit cryptic but tells exactly what is going on:\n\n```\nI0126 21:08:41.151871    3260 fetcher.go:771] Peer c9bd41bc3c6ce895: block #910165 [45f51785…] import failed: block time is in the future: BlockFutureErr, 1453860569 > 1453860551\n```\n\nWhat this means is that the block was received at 21:08:41, but had a timestamp of 21:09:29 (1453860569 unix time, your time zone seems to be UTC-5:00) which is not within to allowed maximum of 30s difference.\n\nTo make a long story very short, it looks like your clock is off by a minute.\n",
